== French ==
# Assets.
# A technical legal/political term, meaning the accumulated body of law and more broadly the achievements of an international organisation, primarily the European Union. However, the term has been increasingly been used in the context of other bodies than the EU, such as the Council of Europe, the WTO, OSCE & the OECD, although this broader use has not so far found the same acceptance as its use for the EU. See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acquis

== English ==
# This term has been accepted into English from French, in the technical French sense (2).